# AAF · Python Style & Safety Rule (MANDATORY)

These are *rules*, not suggestions. Violating them should cause a failing review.

## Types & modernity

- **Target Python 3.11+**. Use `|`-unions, `Self`, `match`, `asyncio.TaskGroup`.
- **Type hints on every function signature** (including `-> None`). Do not use `Any` — use `object` or generics. `Any` is allowed only at validated external boundaries (LLM SDK return types) with an inline comment.
- Pydantic models MUST declare `model_config = ConfigDict(extra="forbid")` for request/response bodies.

## I/O

- All I/O is **async**. Use `async def` + `await`. No `requests`; use `httpx.AsyncClient`.
- Never block the event loop. Use `asyncio.to_thread` for unavoidable sync calls > 10 ms.
- No file I/O at import time.

## Logging

- Use `structlog.get_logger(__name__)`. **Never `print`.** (CI greps for it.)
- Log events as key-value: `log.info("skill.loaded", name=s.name)`. Don't f-string the message.

## Errors

- Raise `backend.core.errors.AAFError` subclasses. Never raise bare `Exception`.
- Never swallow exceptions silently; at minimum `log.exception(...)` before re-raising or converting.

## Dependencies

- Only the libraries already in `pyproject.toml` are allowed unless a PR justifies an addition.
- **Banned**: `langchain`, `langgraph`, `crewai`, `autogen`, `pydantic==1.*`, `requests` (non-test code).

## Style (enforced by ruff)

- Line length ≤ 100.
- Imports: stdlib / third-party / first-party (`backend.*`), blank line between groups.
- f-strings preferred over `.format`/`%`.
- Use `@dataclass(slots=True, frozen=True)` for value objects.

## Layering

- `backend/core/` may NOT import from `backend/agents/`, `backend/workflows/`, or `backend/api/`.
- `backend/api/` may import from `backend/agents/`, `backend/workflows/`, `backend/core/` but NOT vice versa.
- `backend/tests/` can import anything.

## Tests

- Every new module in `backend/core/` or `backend/agents/` has a unit test at `backend/tests/unit/<module_path>.py`.
- Integration tests use `MockLLMProvider`; no real-network tests in CI.

## Enforcement

- `make lint` (ruff) + `make typecheck` (mypy) must pass.
- Pre-commit hook runs `ruff format --check` and `ruff check`.
